import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='adjclose', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['adjclose'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Adj Close: {:.2f}'.format(data['adjclose'].median()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['volume'] = pd.to_numeric(data['volume'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['volume'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='volume', color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Volume: {:.2f}'.format(data['volume'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day
    data['day_of_week'] = data['date'].dt.dayofweek
    data['day_of_week'] = data['day_of_week'].apply(lambda x: 'Monday' if x == 0 else 'Tuesday' if x == 1 else 'Wednesday' if x == 2 else 'Thursday' if x == 3 else 'Friday' if x == 4 else 'Saturday' if x == 5 else 'Sunday')
    data['week_of_year'] = data['date'].dt.weekofyear
    data['week_of_year'] = data['week_of_year'].apply(lambda x: str(x))
    data['high'] = data['high'].astype(float)
    data['low'] = data['low'].astype(float)
    data = data[['year', 'month', 'day', 'day_of_week', 'week_of_year', 'high', 'low']]
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'week_of_year']).agg({'high': 'max', 'low': 'min'}).reset_index()
    data['week_of_year'] = data['week_of_year'].astype(int)
    data = data.sort_values(by=['year', 'week_of_year'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 8))
    sns.barplot(x='week_of_year', y='high', data=data, color='blue', ax=ax)
    sns.barplot(x='week_of_year', y='low', data=data, color='red', ax=ax)
    plt.axhline(y=data['high'].max(), color='blue', linestyle='--', label='Highest price: {:.2f}'.format(data['high'].max()))
    plt.axhline(y=data['low'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Lowest price: {:.2f}'.format(data['low'].min()))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Week of Year')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the highest and lowest price of the stock during the given time period?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

chart = plot(data)
